<td class="" style=""><a href="http://www.fon.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.fon.com/" rel="nofollow">Fon</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>FON</b> (FON Wireless Ltd.) is a company that runs a system of shared <a href="/wiki/Wireless_network" title="Wireless network">wireless networks</a>. The business was launched in November 2005.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>People can become members (called “Foneros” by the company) by agreeing to let FON share their wireless internet connection. Members need to purchase a low-cost wireless router (called “La Fonera”), which acts as a public internet access point; the device also creates a private network that can be used by the owner only. FON members can use any other FON access points free of charge.</p>
<p>Customers who do not share their internet connection (called “Aliens”) can buy internet access from FON for a daily fee. The members whose access points are used by a paying customer receive part of the revenue.</p>
